claim.claim-text:
An intellectual power storing system (2), comprising:
a battery array (4) comprising a plurality of batteries (41), wherein each battery is arranged in a board (52) respectively, the boards (52) used for constructing of a decoration of a building (5);
an indoor-controlling device (3) connected to the battery array (4) and a self-generated power apparatus (1), the indoor-controlling device (3) receiving a power generated by the self-generated power apparatus (1), and storing the power generated by the self-generated power apparatus (1) to the battery array (4) after transforming;
wherein the indoor-controlling device (3) receives and uses a power provided by a power company (6) before a power storing capacity of the battery array (4) reaches a first threshold, the indoor-controlling device (3) instead receives and uses a power provided by the battery array (4) after the power storing capacity of the battery array (4) reaches the first threshold, and the indoor-controlling device (3) stops receiving and using the power provided by the power company (6).

The intellectual power storing system (2) according to claim 3, wherein the indoor-controlling device (3) comprises :
a controlling unit (31);
a power transmitting unit (33) electrically connected to the controlling unit (31) for connecting to the power company (6), the self-generated power apparatus (1) and the battery array (4) for transmitting power;
a power transforming unit (34) electrically connected to the controlling unit (31) for transforming the power generated by the self-generated power apparatus (1);
a power detecting unit (36) electrically connected to the controlling unit (31) and the battery array (4), for monitoring the statuses of the batteries (41) in the battery array (4); and
a switch unit (3) electrically connected the controlling unit (31), the switch unit (3) receiving a trigger for switching the intellectual power storing system (2) on or off.

A method for managing the battery array (4) being used to the intellectual power storing system (2) according to claim 1, the method for managing the battery array (4) comprising:
a) receiving the power provided by the power company (6) for starting operation;
b) receiving and transforming the power generated by the self-generated power apparatus (1), and storing the power generated by the self-generated power apparatus (1) to the battery array (4);
c) determining whether the power storing capacity of the battery array (4) reaches the first threshold;
d) receiving and using the power provided by the battery array (4) when the power storing capacity reaches the first threshold; and
e) stopping receiving and using the power provided by the power company (6) when the power storing capacity reaches the first threshold.

The method for managing the battery array (4) according to claim 10, wherein the method for managing the battery array (4) further comprises following steps:
i1) monitoring the statuses of the batteries (41) of the battery array (4);
i2) generating a connecting architecture of the batteries (41) according to a relationship of a series/parallel connection of the batteries (41), wherein the connecting architecture of the batteries (41) corresponds to a constructing architecture of the boards (52);
i3) searching a location of a failed battery (44) of the batteries (41) according to the relationship of the series/parallel connection of the batteries (41) when a status of one of the batteries (41) is abnormal; and
i4) graphically displaying the connecting architecture and the location of a failed battery (44) of the batteries (41).
